article.headline: Idaho 61, Santa Barbara 50
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Anton Lyons scored 21 points to lead Idaho to a 61-50 victory over UC Santa Barbara on Saturday. The win was third consecutive to open Big West Conference play for the Vandals (5-9, 3-0 Big West) and matches their best Big West start ever. UC Santa Barbara (4-8, 2-3) opened the game with a 6-0 run and was able to stay close most of the night despite dressing just seven players because of injuries. The Gauchos were led by Oliver Chrismen's 12 points and 11 from Derek Rasp. Dandrick Jones finished with 16 points and 10 rebounds for Idaho, which is off to its best start in the Big West since the 1997-98 team opened league play with three straight wins. UC Santa Barbara tied it three times in the second half and took a couple of short-lived leads. The Gauchos tied the game at 47-all with 5:46 to play on a pair of free throws by Glenn Turner, but did not score again for the next 4:45 as Idaho took off on a 13-0 run to seal the game. Seven of Idaho's points in that run were scored at the free-throw line. The Vandals outrebounded the Gauchos 42-29.
